    <div xml:id="PN328">
      <lg type="edition">
<l><gap quantity="4" reason="lost" unit="character"/>ṭaimutaṟ puṟavucērn tirunta</l>
<l>puṉpulac cīṟūr nelviḷai yātē</l>
<l>varakun tiṉaiyu muḷḷavai yellā</l>
<l>miravaṉ mākkaḷuk kīyat tolaintaṉa</l>
<l><gap quantity="24" reason="lost" unit="character"/>ṭamain taṉaṉē</l>
<l>yaṉṉa ṉāyiṉum pāṇa naṉṟum</l>
<l>veḷḷat tiṭumpā luḷḷuṟai tōṭ</l>
<l>kaḷavup puḷiyaṉṉa viḷai<gap quantity="20" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l><gap quantity="26" reason="lost" unit="character"/>vāṭūṉ koḻuṅkuṟai</l>
<l>koykura lariciyoṭu neypey taṭṭut</l>
<l>tuṭuppoṭu civaṇiya kaḷikkoḷ veṇcō</l>
<l>ṟuṇṭiṉi tirunta piṉ<gap quantity="34" reason="lost" unit="character"/></l>
<l><gap quantity="42" reason="lost" unit="character"/>tarukuvaṉ mātō</l>
<l>tāḷimuta ṉīṭiya ciṟunaṟu muññai</l>
<l>muyalvantu kaṟikku muṉṟiṟ</l>
<l>cīṟūr maṉṉaṉaip pāṭiṉai celiṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>  Paddy does not ripen in the little village of grassy fields</l>
<l>that lies in the woodlands…..</l>
<l>All there was of millet and millet</l>
<l>is lost for giving it to the mendicant folks.</l>
<l>………………………….he is suitable.</l>
<l>Even if he is like that, oh bard, ??????</l>
<l>…………………..???????????</l>
<l>after eating delightful white rice gone with the laddle</l>
<l>after cooking [and] pouring ghee along with the rice of plucked ears</l>
<l>with fat pieces of dried meat………………. [and] sitting [there] sweetly,</l>
<l>…………………………will he not give,</l>
<l>if you go after having sung the king of the little village</l>
<l>in the front yard, where the hare comes [and] chews </l>
<l>the little fragrant Muññai grown long at the base of the talipot palm?</l>
</lg>
